    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A suit to recover damages to\nthe amount of $4,000 was begun\nthis morning in Judge Kennan's\ncourt by John T. Carver against\nthe Great Northern Railway Co.\n\n\nTheh complaint states that in\nJanuary, while in the employ of\nthe Cater Transfer Co., plaintiff\nwas unloading a car load of chick\nen- wire from a car spotted on\nsiding in the defendants yards. A\nsudden jerk resulting from the\nhumping of another car caused him\nto fan heavily to the floor of the\ncar in which he was working. in\njuring him severely."
    }
